Kenyans Will Now Be Able To Use Their Mobile Phone Number And A Prefixed Postal Code As Their Mailing Address. This Follow A Partnership Between The Postal Corporation Of Kenya And Mobile Service Provider Safaricom That Aims To Digitize Postal Services Across The Country. The Partnership Comes At A Time When Postal Services Across The Globe Are Experiencing A Decline In Revenues Due To The Adoption Of Online Mailing And Messaging Services And Stiff Completion From Private Courier Services. According To The Postmaster General, The Service Will Generate New Employment Opportunities While Enabling The Postal Corporation To Generate Additional Revenue. ICT Cs Joe Mucheru Lauded The Partnership Noting That It Will Ease The Adoption And Roll Out Of E?Commerce Across The Country.